The point was, that there is a language close to java which can pass objects by value or by reference. (It passes object references by value or by reference if you want to call it like that)<p>To pass an object by reference, it looks exactly like C#&#x27;s out/ref parameter.<p><pre><code>    void function(ref SomeClass arg) {
        arg=null;
    }

    var a=new SomeClass();
    function(a);
    // now a is null
</code></pre>
Which is different from what happens without ref. (or by default in Java)
